---
# Methods & Simulation Pipeline

This document details the computational methods used to validate the DP-ODS alloy.

---

## 1. Activation (Waste Classification)

- **Code:** FISPACT-II (2023 build)  
- **Inputs:** `fispact/DP_ODS.inp`, DEMO divertor neutron spectrum (`spectra/iter_divertor.spc`)  
- **Output metrics:** contact dose rate vs time, 50 y clearance index  
- **Result:** DP-ODS classified as **LLW** (meets DEMO requirement)

---

## 2. Tritium Retention

- **Code:** TMAP7  
- **Inputs:** `tmap7/DP_ODS.inp`, DEMO flux (10²² m⁻²s⁻¹, 873 K)  
- **Output metrics:** total retained tritium, trap depth distribution  
- **Result:** `0.89e17 T/m²` retained after 10⁷ s (passes DEMO target <1.0e17)

---

## 3. Phase Stability

- **Code:** pycalphad (0.9.2)  
- **Database:** SGTE tungsten alloys + user oxide entries  
- **Output metrics:** precipitation stability of Y₂O₃/HfO₂, solubility of Ta  
- **Result:** stable dual oxide dispersion to 1500 °C

---

## 4. Bubble Growth

- **Method:** Object Kinetic Monte Carlo (OKMC) templates (`okmc/dp_ods_template.yaml`)  
- **Parameters:** He injection at 10 appm/s, 900 °C  
- **Result:** <40% bubble size growth vs Y₂O₃-only benchmark

---

## 5. Uncertainty Handling

- ±10% variation in oxide fraction and Ta content tested.  
- DEMO compliance flags remained stable across parametric sweep.
